1
00:00:00,010 --> 00:00:03,980
[Song Shi On | Chu Young Woo]

2
00:00:03,980 --> 00:00:06,940
[Jin Hong Seok | Won Hyung Hoon]

3
00:00:13,360 --> 00:00:17,080
[You Make Me Dance]

4
00:00:17,080 --> 00:00:19,420
[Episode 3]

5
00:00:19,420 --> 00:00:22,060
Mr. Debt-collector?

6
00:00:22,060 --> 00:00:24,140
Why did you come here?

7
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:28,350
Now you're going to come to my house, too? What is it? What more do you want?

8
00:00:28,350 --> 00:00:32,230
Customer. Management.

9
00:00:33,910 --> 00:00:36,970
What do you mean by customer management? You're probably just here to collect money.

10
00:00:36,970 --> 00:00:40,420
Look here, I've had an extremely terrible day today.

11
00:00:40,420 --> 00:00:44,070
I've been chased by you since the morning. The partner I trusted cut ties with me.

12
00:00:44,070 --> 00:00:46,310
And the only barre I had, broke.

13
00:00:46,310 --> 00:00:50,540
But it's my birthday today.

14
00:00:51,060 --> 00:00:56,170
So who the hell are you, to torture me like this all day long!

15
00:01:04,860 --> 00:01:07,510
[Delicious Cake]

16
00:01:09,190 --> 00:01:12,800
Happy birthday.

17
00:01:15,050 --> 00:01:16,840
Congrats.

18
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:43,720
Blow the candle.

19
00:01:43,720 --> 00:01:45,650
Why should I?

20
00:01:56,480 --> 00:01:58,970
How did you know it was my birthday today?

21
00:02:01,700 --> 00:02:04,070
Article 1, Section 1, of the debt-collector's policy:

22
00:02:04,070 --> 00:02:08,570
"Know the debtor from inside out."

23
00:02:08,570 --> 00:02:10,330
The what policy now?

24
00:02:10,330 --> 00:02:13,750
Turns out you aren't a debt-collector but a stalker.

25
00:02:18,380 --> 00:02:21,630
Your taste is quite... unique.

26
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:23,750
You should try it once. It's delicious.

27
00:02:23,750 --> 00:02:27,330
No thanks. Do you think I've never been fooled before?

28
00:02:37,230 --> 00:02:39,180
Don't you have hands?

29
00:02:43,620 --> 00:02:49,470
Did you know that you have a talent for being warm one moment and cold the next?

30
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:51,760
You've got such a weird personality.

31
00:03:01,750 --> 00:03:04,730
Write down the name of your guarantor.

32
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:10,050
[Surety Contract]

33
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:17,220
I don't have one. I am responsible for myself.

34
00:03:21,630 --> 00:03:23,730
You have your mom.

35
00:03:38,980 --> 00:03:42,420
I don't want to. Never.

36
00:03:46,370 --> 00:03:50,900
Even if I had a knife to my throat, I'd never bring my mom into this matter.

37
00:03:50,900 --> 00:03:54,660
Where did you spend all that money?

38
00:03:54,660 --> 00:03:57,670
You borrowed it as soon as you turned twenty.

39
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:01,920
It's a secret.

40
00:04:02,550 --> 00:04:06,700
What was it? Entertainment? Or maybe luxury goods?

41
00:04:06,700 --> 00:04:08,380
Or gambling?

42
00:04:09,630 --> 00:04:12,830
I'm a model student.

43
00:04:12,830 --> 00:04:14,950
Did your mom take it?

44
00:04:14,950 --> 00:04:19,030
No, that's definitely not it.

45
00:04:21,030 --> 00:04:23,340
My mom isn't that kind of a person.

46
00:04:23,340 --> 00:04:25,470
They say strong denial is acknowledgment.

47
00:04:25,470 --> 00:04:27,590
I told you it's not like that!

48
00:04:29,970 --> 00:04:33,630
My mom remarried and went to Switzerland.

49
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:35,890
So that's why...

50
00:04:35,890 --> 00:04:38,880
That's why...

51
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:43,310
I gave it to her to support the development of her relationship!

52
00:04:43,310 --> 00:04:46,550
I'm telling you, my mom isn't that kind of mom.

53
00:04:48,630 --> 00:04:50,510
So you've been abandoned.

54
00:04:50,510 --> 00:04:54,330
Dammit. Mr. Debt-collector,

55
00:04:54,330 --> 00:04:58,600
you sure speak nicely. I wasn't abandoned.

56
00:05:05,050 --> 00:05:08,800
This is my mom. She's pretty, isn't she?

57
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:14,380
I forgot it's her wedding anniversary today.

58
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:19,800
My birthday is on my mom's wedding anniversary.

59
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:24,200
And my mom's wedding anniversary is on my birthday.

60
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,680
Come here for a second.

61
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:38,740
I want to send a celebratory picture to her. So she doesn't worry.

62
00:05:38,740 --> 00:05:40,700
Come on. Like we're close.

63
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:44,400
Come on smile a bit. Just like this.

64
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:49,160
That's pretty. One, two, three.

65
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:55,100
It came out pretty good.

66
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:02,420
♫ I felt like love  ♫

67
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:04,700
♫ didn’t exist  ♫

68
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:08,330
♫ When I made my timid confession ♫

69
00:06:08,330 --> 00:06:12,790
[Mom! How is the weather over there? It's freezing here.]
[I miss you.]
[I had to eat alone today ㅠㅠ]

70
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:16,570
♫ You smiled brightly at me, just like in a dream ♫

71
00:06:16,570 --> 00:06:22,640
♫ You turned a blind eye to my shortcomings ♫

72
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:28,370
♫ And stayed by me so I could stand back up ♫

73
00:06:28,370 --> 00:06:33,610
♫ I love you. If there is one person ♫

74
00:06:33,610 --> 00:06:39,850
♫ That fate has meant for me, then it is you ♫

75
00:06:39,850 --> 00:06:46,440
♫ Who is smiling before me now I am so happy ♫

76
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:50,410
[2021 Korea International Contemporary Dance Audition Between Us]

77
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:53,840
- Do you have a way to guarantee that you'll get the lead role?
- My dance.

78
00:06:56,330 --> 00:07:01,200
All the while I watched his dance, my heart was pounding.

79
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:04,780
As for the reason, I don't know.

80
00:07:14,390 --> 00:07:17,940
Maybe it's because he's lonely, just like me.

81
00:07:17,940 --> 00:07:23,050
Or maybe, it's the innocence in his eyes which I don't have.

82
00:07:24,030 --> 00:07:27,840
If it isn't that either,

83
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:32,390
then maybe it is his never-faltering arrogance.

84
00:07:56,430 --> 00:08:00,020
[Byeol, Star, Etoile - Live Podcast]

85
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:05,200
♫ I love you. If this is a dream, ♫

86
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:09,240
♫ Then I want to stay asleep forever ♫

87
00:08:11,530 --> 00:08:18,650
♫ Just like in a never-ending dream,
Please always stay by my side  ♫

88
00:08:18,650 --> 00:08:21,550
I decided to put my trust

89
00:08:21,550 --> 00:08:24,400
in his dance.

90
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:28,310
And in his dream.

91
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:32,240
[Surety Contract]
[Jin Hong Seok]

92
00:09:08,530 --> 00:09:10,260
What's this?

93
00:09:11,070 --> 00:09:14,180
- You're up?
- You didn't go home yesterday?

94
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:17,420
Don't you know, "The early bird catches the worm?"

95
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:19,800
Your audition is just around the corner! Get ready!

96
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:25,030
What are you saying? Besides, what crime did the early worm commit?

97
00:09:25,030 --> 00:09:30,090
Never mind that. This isn't right. You can't do as you please just because you're a debt-collector.

98
00:09:30,090 --> 00:09:32,630
Hurry up and get out of my house!

99
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:45,760
Wash up.

100
00:09:49,350 --> 00:09:51,290
Hey!

101
00:09:52,910 --> 00:09:55,320
Go and wash up, right away.

102
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:13,510
Sit.

103
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:29,020
Aren't you going to eat?

104
00:10:31,830 --> 00:10:35,560
I can't have carbs or fat. I'm only allowed proteins.

105
00:10:44,670 --> 00:10:46,520
Just what do you do?

106
00:10:46,520 --> 00:10:49,370
I’m a debt-collector, of course.

107
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:12,600
Hey.

108
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:17,730
You're not going to do this every morning, are you? It makes me really uncomfortable.

109
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:28,990
- Hello.
- Answer your phone whenever I call you.

110
00:11:31,940 --> 00:11:35,060
Also, how good are you as compared to your classmates?

111
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:38,390
I'm not sure, I'd say, maybe the second-best.

112
00:11:38,390 --> 00:11:39,900
Who's the best then?

113
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:43,670
There's this senior of mine. Lee Jung Hoon.

114
00:11:43,670 --> 00:11:45,730
Is he going to audition, too?

115
00:11:45,730 --> 00:11:47,600
- Of course, he is.
- In that case,

116
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:51,210
your goal is to catch up to that guy now. Okay?

117
00:11:51,990 --> 00:11:55,080
That won't be easy though.

118
00:12:07,410 --> 00:12:13,130
I have your back. You remember what trust is to a debtor and his creditor?

119
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:20,380
[You Make Me Dance]

120
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:25,970
♫ Your tone was a little different than usual ♫

121
00:12:25,970 --> 00:12:30,680
♫ I feel like we're breaking up ♫

122
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:36,840
♫ Can we please just move on for now? ♫
